Variability. Size of males ranging from 8.1–8.4 mm , size of females from 8.5–9.5 mm . Clypeus 2.2–2.5 times as wide as long, antennal club of the male 0.91–0.94 as long as the clypeus width. Sides of the pronotum either slightly concave in the distal portion or straight. Shape of parameres (
Fig. 15
) variable, especially in lateral view. No other relevant variation was observed on the small number of examined specimens.
